programme.title: On the Front Line
programme.desc: Real human bodies are used every day by UK universities to teach students and medical professionals about anatomy. Go behind the scenes at Cardiff University to meet the staff and students who work with body donors every day. Meet the office manager whose job includes embalming bodies, the student inspired to become a doctor after losing her best friend to cancer, and the lecturer who thinks she has the best job in the world.
